e Norwegian explorer, Fridtjof Nansen; the liberal British campaigner and MP of the 1940s, Eleanor Rathbone; reflections on the lives and images of spinsters. The text is supplemented and interrupted throughout by images (photographs, paintings, facsimile documents), some of which serve to illustrate the story, others engaging indirectly with the written word.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aArt and society. 0aArt criticszEnglandzManchester. 0aJewish familiesvBiography. 0aJewish familieszEngland. 0aJewsxSocial conditionsy20th centuryvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Literary.2bisacsh1 aWolff, Janet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/9781526121295?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526121295zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526121295/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA